“Patience sister, I’m not quite skilled enough to try to make that Dark Prince Regent Breastplate yet.  And you wouldn’t want me to botch the attempt and ruin the components, especially since some of those items were rather costly and hard to find.”<br>
Salura sighs and unconsciously shifts her weight and fidgets with her battle worn gear. “How much more practice will you need?”<br>
“Quite a bit, I’m afraid.  Keep gathering Acrylia, windstones, and essences of wind..  I’ll practice making the Acrylia armors until I’m confidant I can make your items.  We can sell the Acrylia and make some money back.  And tell Gospasha to get cranking on those vials of clear mana”<br>
“She knows, she hasn’t yet attained that level of magic.  She and Kynaen from the “Holy Warriors of Faith” will be training these next few days.  When Gos attains here 29th level of proficiency, you’ll have a constant flow of mana for your smithing tempers.”<br>
“Ok Salura.  Oh, I’ll also need some money, armor molds aren’t cheap.  And until the family store sells some of your equipment, we’re pretty much broke.”<br>
“Well, we could sell your drogmor…Ugly, smelly beast.  Then again, I’m sure we won’t get much back for him.”<br>
“Oh no you don’t!  I love that beast!  He may not be the fastest animal, but I’ve grown to count on him.  He intimidates our foes just enough to make them think twice about hitting me while I meditate in battle.  And it gives me a good view of the battle.”<br>
“I was only kidding brother.  The Drog stays.  It’s just that your smithing components are very expensive.  Have you seen the prices in the Bazaar lately?”<br>
“Yes, but once I make some Acrylia armor, we will make some money back.  Our merchant reports that we sold over 3k plat today.  I told her to use that money and buy the reasonably priced items I need.”<br>
“Ok, when you run out of smithing components, join me and we’ll hunt the beasts for more.  To change the subject, I received a message from Kenronous from “One of the Chosen.  We are both negotiating on our clan rejoining with the OotC.  It seems the reasons for our departure have been dealt with.”<br>
“Then I say we rejoin.  Or is it not as simple as that?”<br>
“Well, Salur, we did leave quietly, with no word.  Although I burnt no bridges, I’m sure they are just as hesitant to offer a position as we are to accept.”<br>
“It would be nice to be guilded again.  I could use some help in completing my quests. No offense sister, but we need more than just your blade to succeed. And I know you miss your friends Merk, Audry, Hurb and Nul.  And I know I miss hitting the dungeons with them.”<br>
“Well, then it’s settled.  If an offer is tendered, then we will accept.  In fact, we may know as soon as this weekend.  I know our names are being discussed by the officers.”<br>
“Oh, that’s why my ears are ringing.  I thought it was from the hammer hitting the anvil for too long.  I fear I’m losing my hearing from all this smithing.”<br>
